When channel 3 is turned off using the bit in the NR30 register, it outputs 0v.<br />If shift is set to 0% (&gt;&gt;4) it outputs -1v.<br />(at least I THINK this is right... blargg?)<br /><br />LN<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=399">Lord Nightmare</a> — Tue Sep 29, 2009 8:41 am</p><hr />
